The paper focuses on analyzing user activity in Question and Answer (Q&A) instances, which is related to social computing (cs.SOC) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The authors also mention the use of quantitative methods to better understand and control communities, which could fall under the categories of social informatics (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the study involves clustering and modeling user behavior, which could be related to data mining (cs.SD).
